REF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umoltaenyadmagmus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moltaenya D Magmus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 10:51:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Disappointed</span><hr size=1> I am very disappointed in the actions of a 60 cleric named Golems.  <br>
<br>
Yesterday (9/25), he ran a &quot;rush pick up&quot; naggy raid after the patch.  I found out about this and was a little upset, because Gorndax had posted that he, Razzmataz, and myself, were going to run a raid for old times sake, and to have a little fun and meet some new people.  I told Golems that I was upset about this, because I had seen his name on this board under &quot;Dragons and Planes&quot; and figured he decided to race me to Naggy.  He told me that he had no knowledge of this raid and felt bad about it, so that I should come and bring whomever I had signed up along with me.  So Gorndax, myself, and our cleric buddy made our way to Sol B.  <br>
<br>
Turns out there was a major wipe out in the room before the FG throne room.  Reason being was that someone was pulling LDCs, and well....goofed.  Nothing got mezzed because there<br>
were no enchanters.  Then I heard after my rez from the wipeout that someone had ninja-ed the Warlord (not <br>
sure if this is true or not).  At this moment I probably should have just walked away, but no, I wanted to see<br>
if this was going to be successful or not.  <br>
<br>
We make it inside the throne room, and pull a variety of LDCs and FGs.  No one knows who the MA was, things got rather messy.  There were no set up groups for the FGs either.  We ended up having 2 clerics in our group and one shaman...meanwhile the other 8 warriors and few tanks had to share 2 clerics.  Our clerics ended up healing others..but I found it odd that we had 2 in our group.  <br>
<br>
Finally..we make it to the stairs before the buff room.  At this point I discovered that Golems had a monk named Jaky.  I thought &quot;Hmmm, where does this name sound familiar from?&quot;  Well I figured it out.  This was the same Jaky that was in EC asking if anyone had Naggy scheduled.  This Jaky got a reply from Oobidoob that there was, and I ooc'ed it as well.  Then I thought, &quot;Hmm, he lied to me about knowing..&quot;  <br>
<br>
Well, we finally got all the FGs cleared and proceeded to buffing.  In chat..it took forever for people to get there...our buffs were done horribly wrong, and things were not explained to everyone.  And those poor people on their first dragon raid had no idea what was going on... Basically, groups were set up no one knew what their role was and we were told this, &quot;Dararu pulls him to the door, everyone runs behind him, nuke at 60%&quot;  <br>
<br>
Well, we failed needless to say.  People were tired, because it was about 2am EST when this happened.  So I told people that I had a raid scheduled for tomorrow anyways, and that we should probably try again then when everyone is awake and has motivation.  Then Golems decided to go again.  (Well most of the raid left, but they did succeed at 5am EST I was told.)  Anyhow, when people were leaving, Golems had told the zone that there was an emergency patch that night and no one should worry because he would be up again tomorrow(which I thought was a lie from the beginning but I chose to believe him since it was late and I was tired).  Then others started saying that.  Lie number two of course.  <br>
<br>
Came into the game this morning asking if Naggy was up, he was not.  I talked to a guildie of his, they said the only reason he did that raid was so his twink monk could get the gloves.  Interesting...and there was rumor going on during the raid that these people who came along were being used.  I also heard from this person that Golems had neglected to attend or help out on a different raid (this part I am not so clear on).  Anyhow, I will not hold Golems lying actions against his guild for just this reason, that he seems to be separated from it.<br>
<br>
Golems, I suggest you apologize to those people you let down who signed up for my raid.  I suggest you apologize to me as well, for lying to me.  I can only hope that you let these people know that you used them for your own personal gain.  And I also hope that you can learn some respect.<br>
<br>
-Moltie<br>
<br>
I can expect many people to question this, and yes I have answers for you all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 11:07:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> I'm really surprised to hear this.  Golems is a pretty good guy, and I've heard that he knows what he's doing on dragon raids.  This raid sounds like it was really rushed and sloppy.  It makes me wonder whether there was someone behind the scenes who was eager to start a Ragefire camp.  It wouldn't be the first time that some questionable things have been done for that reason. That's just speculation, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umoltaenyadmagmus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moltaenya D Magmus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 11:11:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> Yes I have heard that this isn't normal of him to do either.  I asked a few times about Ragefire during the night, and obviously he didn't need him since he had the epic.  I got no response as to who wanted it.  This morning when I logged in someone was at the druid rings in LS wondering if Rage was taken, I went into Sol B and checked things out and I didnt *see* anyone there...so no idea about that at all.  <br>
<br>
-Moltie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uguildon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Guildon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 11:18:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> Did I miss something or were the level maximums removed from Nags and Vox while I was gone? How does a 60 cleric organize a Nag raid when there is level limit of 52? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujaedengrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaeden Grae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 488<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 11:25:57 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.covad.net/~blcktail/2SDOGc.gif width=96 height=85></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> While it sucks, I will point out several problems I have with you blaming Golems..<br>
