Same way everyone else does. Stay outta agro range <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uunclegorndax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uncle Gorndax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 11:38:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> Just to correct a misunderstanding from Jaeden.  Moltaenya did not run a raid last night, nor did it fail.  Golems first attempt faid in which Moltaenya was present (and so was I).  I have more I wish to comment on later, but im at work.  <br>
<br>
Gorndax <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uunclegorndax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uncle Gorndax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 1:13:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> The three of us (Moltaenya, Razzmataz, Myself) wanted to run the raid tomorrow, thinking the patch would have ended much later.  Golems rushed us, it happens.  Not everyone has the same respect standards.  I sure as hell never did that when I raided dragons, and i remember precisly a large discussion about a problem Crinkle caused trying to undermine Razzmataz's raid way back about 6 months ago.  Same thing happened to Adarian who took the day off of work to run a raid and was rushed by someone else.  <br>
<br>
If someone saw the boards which I know golems did as he posted a raid for the earlier patches, normally if you see something that might be a conflict you would inform them.  As that was the whole purpose of the board, and not for reserving them.  Foeb used to contact me if he wanted to do something like that, and it was polite and I never once said anything but GL to him.  <br>
<br>
He lied about the patch(tried to ensure us it was going in), he used people as cannonfodder to get a twink a dragon item, he lied to us not knowning about the raid.  Additionally, after the failed attempt I wouldnt have thought anything... except I invited him to ours later that day.  Instead of just packing bags after the resses and realizing that he could do it just as decent later he ignored our invites.  <br>
<br>
Greed gets the best of some I suppose.  I just remember when those raids were fun and exciting to take them down with tactics.  Im more upset for the fact that something like this has to pop up again and leaves the other 20 people out of a hope today.  <br>
<br>
Gorndax <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udeeliinukrack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deeliin Ukrack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 1:27:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> Pretty bad when me the only enchanter there was lvl 41.<br>
