<br>
No one's saying Moltaenya was &quot;reserving&quot; anything, but it's rather disrespecting just to butt in ahead of someone like that.  You've all read about it, and lots of people have agreed about it time and time again so there isn't really reason to say that's not disrespecting of Golems.  I've known Golems for quite a long time, and no that's not how I'd expect him to act.<br>
<br>
 <p>ChamCham Silverstar -- Lvl 60 Phantasmist<BR>Zelgadis Greyweather -- Lvl 52 Pathfinder<BR>Evil never did stand a chance!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usircrombattleaxe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir CromBattleAxe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 2:19:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> Deeliin your wrong this is not what happens at pick up raids. This is what happens at lemming runs. <br>
<br>
Honestly I am not suprised at this happening however I feel it necessary to point out a little detail.<br>
<br>
Golems little brother plays the same account sometimes and has been known to use his big brothers characters without permission. I know this as I helped him kill naggy and camp rage fire for his epic. Golems has never killed himself with a mana stone however his little brother has 3 times that I know of. Same character different players = multiple personalities. <br>
<br>
This is no excuse and I sure as hell do not approve of the lemming run that this turned into. Everyone should have left when they looked at how the groups were set up and the lack of needed classes. I think Gorndax showing up added credibility to the raid chances of succeeding and led people to believe they couldn’t fail with him present. <br>
<br>
AKA False confidence Example:<br>
<br>
I made the same mistake ONCE. I showed up to a lemming run said WTF are you people doing and stood back and watched with a afk message up that I am not leading I am not in the raid and if you think you will win your wrong. <br>
<br>
The leader led 40 people up the wrong ramps in vox's lair and wouldn’t listen to the people that knew what they were doing. The people that had never been on a dragon raid wouldn’t listen and some of the experienced dragon raiders even figured with the numbers they would be fine. <br>
<br>
People started asking me what was going on with the CR and I had to put up the afk message &quot; gravethumb got a res ported out and logged out &quot; if you want your body summoned bring 150 plat and get your ass back in zone.<br>
<br>
Spent 6 hours and a lot of plat covering the CR with Honir and found out half the people on the raid were personal invites from Gravethumb and were under level 45. Next week Gravethumb tried naggy. I stayed the hell away and had allot of fun without worrying about it. Wipeout and he did the same damn thing.<br>
<br>
The lesson here is if you think it is going to be bad LEAVE you have only yourself to blame if you stay and it goes bad.<br>
<br>
CromBattleAxe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uelwyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elwyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 573<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 2:21:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> Does Nagafen, Ninja-looting and a monk named Jaky give anyone besides me a strange sense of deja vu?<br>
