<br>
How did someone come to the conclusion that he had a monk that was present anyway? <p>Tormentcia

55 Warrior and Officer of the Silvermist Wolves</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uemberial.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emberial</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.home.net/killgasm/curley_sm_clr.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 3:18:43 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/doublebass/emberial2.jpg width=176 height=322></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disappointed</span><hr size=1> I think I was part of the second raid led by Golems last night. it was about 1am pst when I joined. BTW, we did NOT kill Naggy. This was my first Naggy raid. If I could have gated tho I would have...as soon as I found out we had no chanters, 2 clerics, and 1 shammy (Straif) who would be there for the actual Naggy run (Thanks Voom for all the buffs...***HUG***). At this point I don't think we had any Druids.<br>
<br>
My guildmate Straif and I ended up joining. Straif was told by a warrior, Dararu, that he would be in on the roll for a CoF if he joined (Straif is a 49 shammy...but his main is a monk). Later in the chatroom, Golems told me in private that he never did that. So there is one lie (don't know who's exactly).<br>
<br>
When I showed up I got summoned to the FG room. Everyone was milling about like cattle. No grps were made for Fgs...we just kind of formed our own. <br>
<br>
As far as I can tell, all loot was randomed..so that was atleast good. There seemed to be ALOT of downtime between FG pulls. I think about 3 hrs total until all FGs were dead. I know at one point there was atleast a 30 minute downtime as I had to recast Call of Sky 4 times (10 minute duration).<br>
<br>
I don't know what was up with the buffline. FR ended up being 3rd down. I'm pretty sure that is kind of important. I thought the crap buffs were supposed to go first? The buffline took twice as long as it should have for the amount of ppl that were there (my experience coming from working with Kerna's Vox raid last week <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). I think because no crack and only one Necro to twitch. *sigh*. <br>
<br>
In the chatroom we were told that all the healers would be in one group to heal Dararu, who was the only one to taunt. O.K. I don't know if this is good strat or not as, like I said, this was my first Naggy raid. Took a long time for all to get in, too, because Golems recruited 2 druids for the zergling rush.<br>
<br>
So at about 5am PST we were all wiped out. I got no notice that corpses were being recovered..so I interrupted a druid and Nec in my guild from their game time to help out. Turns out not needed, but would have been nice to know something was being done. <br>
<br>
Well the CR ended up being a nightmare, for me and Straif. I got rezzed by Golems. As he was rezzing I sent him a tell that Straif had to log and I had his acct...so I needed to get a TP out of there so I could log on Straif for a rez. No answer. Rinse and repeat a few times. Finally I had to start saying it in /ooc. Finally just logged Straif on my husbands computer (hate having to run between two computers in a dangerous zone). Jaxxelia (sorry..forgot your name exactly) was kind enough to get me a TP out. During this time Golems had logged...4 or 5 ppl still needed a rez but had either camped or were afk...but Straif was ready to go. Found out later that Golems had rezzed Soulbring, our other cleric, and she gated. So no rez for Jaky...and he was pissed. Well, fine. Ended up having Voom pull Straifs corpse to the zone while I logged on Zendell, my husbands 52 Cleric, and ran him from NRO to Solb to rez Straif. In the meantime I sent about 12 tells to Jaky to consent Voom and I would rez him with Zen. No answer. After a small mishap for Voom (Did I mention you are my HERO??), I ended up Rezing both Voom and Straif..and Banisheol who was one of the corpses left behind by Golems (she got a summon from a Nec at the zone). One last tell to Jaky and Golems (logged apparently). 6am. time for bed.<br>
<br>
I don't know if all the corpses got found. Umbrae (nec in guild) offered to come do summons but Golems said he'd get everyone.<br>
<br>
It was definitely an..experience. So how does a good Naggy raid go? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
